{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"Available Plugins","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Display Reward Point</p> </li> <li> <p>Bundle Discount </p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/","title":"nopAccelerate Plus Pro","text":"<p>nopAccelerate Plus Pro helps businesses across the nopCommerce ecosystem create highly relevant, scalable, and lightning-fast in-site search and product discovery experiences.</p> <p>It is one of the Best Rich Search Plugins for nopCommerce stores. It integrates Apache Solr with nopCommerce to deliver outstanding features that enhance in-site product search.</p> <p>nopAccelerate Plus Pro brings powerful search technology that strengthens your eCommerce store search, ultimately improving user experience and driving customer satisfaction.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#why-nopaccelerate-plus-pro","title":"Why nopAccelerate Plus Pro?","text":"<ul> <li>Better and faster search results directly and positively impact sales.  </li> <li>Better Search = More Revenue!</li> <li>nopAccelerate Plus Pro is completely different from the original nopAccelerate.   Since 2013\u201314, nopCommerce has evolved significantly, allowing us to design an advanced, modern, and standard integration plugin.</li> <li>The product is now more compatible with themes and plugins, easier to extend, and simpler to maintain.</li> <li>It includes Search &amp; Facets features, making it more powerful than nopAccelerate Plus Search.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#core-features","title":"Core Features","text":"<ol> <li>DIH (Data Import Handler) indexing process for faster indexing.</li> <li>Reload Solr core directly from the admin panel.</li> <li>Automatic core setup (managed schema, DIH request, update dbConfig, schema management).</li> <li>Clear core data from the nopAccelerate Plus Pro admin panel.</li> <li>Execute Solr queries from the admin panel.</li> <li>Automatic indexing on entity change via a simple toggle setting.</li> <li>Direct DB update support with automatic incremental table update.</li> <li>Basic configuration panel integrated into nopCommerce admin.</li> <li>Single core for multi-language &amp; multi-store.</li> <li>API integration support.</li> <li>Advanced wizard for Solr setup &amp; product integration.</li> <li>Easy-to-follow product basics and admin settings tour.</li> <li>Zero theme customization required.</li> <li>Supports 36 languages out of the box.</li> <li>Fully compatible with NopTemplates themes.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#search-features","title":"Search Features","text":"<ol> <li>Replaces default nopCommerce search.</li> <li>Extensive configuration options for search relevancy.</li> <li>Advanced language analysis during search.</li> <li>Search across Meta Title, Description &amp; Keywords.</li> <li>Auto spell suggestions.</li> <li>Sorting options in search results.</li> <li>Infinite scrolling and pagination options.</li> <li>Fine-tuning search using Minimum Should Match.</li> <li>Highly relevant and advanced search functionality.</li> <li>Advanced autocomplete search with greater relevancy.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#catalog-features","title":"Catalog Features","text":"<ol> <li>Product navigation from Apache Solr.</li> <li>Layered / Faceted navigation.</li> <li>Enhanced Category, Manufacturer &amp; Tag pages via Solr.</li> <li>Configurable catalog listing options.</li> <li>Stay online during first-time full indexing.</li> <li>Support for default filters.</li> <li>Category page filters.</li> <li>Manufacturer page filters.</li> <li>Product Tag page filters.</li> <li>jQuery slider-based price range filter.</li> <li>Multi-select faceting.</li> <li>Enhanced faceting UI.</li> <li>Instant AJAX faceting.</li> <li>AJAX response caching.</li> <li>Solr request caching.</li> <li>Stock availability filter.</li> <li>Rating-based sorting.</li> <li>Mobile-responsive filters.</li> <li>Infinite scrolling on all catalog pages.</li> <li>State-aware URLs using HTML5 History API.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#facet-features","title":"Facet Features","text":"<ol> <li>Price Range and Price Slot facet filters.</li> <li>Category, Manufacturer, Vendor &amp; Product Tag facet filters.</li> <li>Product Attribute &amp; Specification Attribute facet filters.</li> <li>Stock Availability filter.</li> <li>Product Rating facet filter.</li> <li>Instant AJAX faceting.</li> <li>Search within facet results.</li> <li>View More / View Less functionality for long facet lists.</li> <li>Default expanded or collapsed facet settings on page load.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/CreateCore/","title":"Creating a new Core","text":"<p>After installing and starting Solr, you can connect to the client (web interface) of Solr. You can verify the setup and installation simply by running solr on the port you specified. We have created core on 8983 port so we can access localhost:8983/solr/#/ on any browser.</p> <p></p> <p>As highlighted in the above screen shot, initially there are no cores in Apache Solr. Now, we will see how to create a core in Solr.</p> <p>A simple way is to create command (solr create -c Solr_sample -p 8983) as shown below:</p> <p>Here, we are trying to create a core named Solr_sample in Apache Solr. This command creates a core displaying the following message.</p> <p></p> <p>You can create multiple cores in Solr. On the left-hand side of the Solr Admin, you can see a core selector where you can select the newly created core, as shown in the following screenshot.</p> <p>To check the created core, you can look at C:\\Solr\\server\\solr\\Solr_sample location</p> <p>[Important Note : If your Solr is hosted on shared server then you need to follow steps to make nopAccelerate Plus workable.]</p> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/DeleteCore/","title":"How to Delete Core","text":"<p>You can delete core using the delete command of Apache Solr.</p> <p>Let\u2019s suppose we have a core named my_core in Solr, as shown below :</p> <p></p> <p>You can delete this core using the delete command by passing the name of the core to this command as follows :</p> <p>solr delete -c my_core -p 8983</p> <p>On executing the above command, the specified core will be deleted displaying the following message.</p> <p></p> <p>You can open the web interface of Solr to verify whether the core has been deleted or not.</p> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/DeleteIndexData/","title":"How to Delete Indexed data","text":"<p>If you want to delete data from the Solr Index then you just need to simply run a single query in browser.</p> <p>http://://update?stream.body=:&amp;commit=true <p>Let us see an example:</p> <p>Suppose, I have a core with name \"Solr_sample\" and my solr server is running on port 8983, then the query will be:</p> <p>http://localhost:8983/solr/Solr_sample/update?stream.body=:&amp;commit=true</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/","title":"JAVA Setup","text":"<p>To set up SOLR and nopAccelerate Plus on your machine, the first step is to install and configure Java. Follow the steps below:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#1-download-and-install-java","title":"1. Download and Install Java","text":"<p>Download JAVA Latest Version from here.</p> <p>Install the latest Java version. You may choose the version as per your system requirements, but we recommend using the Windows Offline (64-bit) installer.</p> <p>After successful installation, you can check the Java installation path:</p> <ul> <li> <p>For Windows 32-bit: <code>C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Java</code></p> </li> <li> <p>For Windows 64-bit: <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java</code></p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_1","title":"JAVA Setup","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#2-define-the-java_home-environment-variable","title":"2. Define the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> Environment Variable","text":"<p>Defining the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> variable helps SOLR locate the Java installation on your machine.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#a-open-environment-variable-settings","title":"a) Open Environment Variable Settings","text":"<p>Do one of the following:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Windows 7:   Right-click My Computer \u2192 Properties \u2192 Advanced System Settings</p> </li> <li> <p>Windows 8:   Control Panel \u2192 System \u2192 Advanced System Settings</p> </li> <li> <p>Windows 10 / 11:   Search for Environment Variables \u2192 Select Edit the system environment variables</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#b-click-the-environment-variables-button","title":"b) Click the Environment Variables button.","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_2","title":"JAVA Setup","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#c-under-system-variables-click-new","title":"c) Under System Variables, click New.","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_3","title":"JAVA Setup","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#d-add-the-java_home-variable","title":"d) Add the JAVA_HOME Variable","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Variable Name: <code>JAVA_HOME</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Variable Value:   Add your Java installation path, for example: <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jre1.8.0_201</code></p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_4","title":"JAVA Setup","text":"<p>Click OK. You will now see the newly added <code>JAVA_HOME</code> variable in the environment variables list.</p> <p></p> <p>You have successfully configured the Java environment variable.</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ReloadCore/","title":"How to Reload Core","text":"<p>You can reload core simply by selecting core and reload from Solr admin, please check below screenshot for more detail.</p> <p>This can be useful when any changes have been made to your solrconfig.xml or schema.xml files.</p> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLR/","title":"What is SOLR ?","text":"<p>Solr is popular, blazing fast, open source NoSQL search platform from the Apache Lucene project. Solr is highly scalable, providing fault tolerant distributed search and indexing. It powers the search and navigation features of many of the world's largest Internet sites.  </p> <p>Some of the Major features of Solr are as below :</p> <ol> <li>Powerful full-text search</li> <li>Hit highlighting</li> <li>Faceted search</li> <li>Dynamic clustering</li> <li>Database integration</li> </ol> <p>To know more about Solr feature please check here . Once you get basic idea regarding Solr, you can start Solr setup on your end.</p> <p>Let us start with Solr setup on your machine.</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/","title":"SOLR Setup","text":"<p>To set up SOLR on your machine, follow the steps below:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#1-download-solr","title":"1. Download Solr","text":"<p>Go to this link and download Solr 8.11.0 or above:</p> <p>\ud83d\udc49 Download Solr</p> <p>Select the preferred file. We recommend downloading Solr 8.11.0 version.</p> <p>We are assuming you are installing this on Windows.</p> <p>Note: The <code>solr-version.zip</code> or <code>solr-version.tgz</code> files (where version is the version number, e.g., <code>7.5.0</code>) contain: - Apache Solr - HTML documentation - Solr tutorial  </p> <p></p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#_1","title":"Solr Setup Steps","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#2-copy-downloaded-solr-version","title":"2. Copy Downloaded Solr Version","text":"<p>Extract the downloaded file to a preferred location.</p> <p>We assume you extracted it to the C:\\ drive and named the folder Solr. So your Solr path becomes:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#_2","title":"Solr Setup Steps","text":"<p>Hence, Solr is downloaded and Java is set up. Now let's start Solr.</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/StartSolr/","title":"How to Start/Stop/Restart SOLR ?","text":"<p>We are expecting that you have completed Java Setup and download Solr on your machine.</p> <p>To start the Solr Server, all you need is to run few commands on your command prompt. Assuming you have extracted the Solr folder to</p> <p>\"C:\\Solr\"</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/StartSolr/#1-open-command-prompt-and-execute-below-commands","title":"1. Open Command prompt and execute below commands","text":"<p>[Note: You can also start solr on system startup, please check steps here.]</p> <p>a) select the location of bin folder of c:/ &gt; solr &gt; bin</p> <p></p> <p>b) You can start Solr using command : solr start -p 8983, Once your solr is started you can move forward for Creating New Core</p> <p>Here, -p specifies the port number on which your solr server will run.</p> <p></p> <p>c) You can stop Solr using command : solr stop -p 8983</p> <p></p> <p>d) You can restart Solr using command : solr restart -p 8983</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/StartSolronSystemStartup/","title":"Start Solr on System Startup","text":"<p>Question:</p> <p>How to use Solr as service in window server ?</p> <p>Solution:</p> <p>If you want to use Solr as service in window server, please take guideline from here</p> <p>Things to take care :</p> <ul> <li>Solr is not down when log-off from system.</li> <li>System restart should automatically start Solr on same port that we have configured in service.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SupportDocOverview/","title":"Support Document","text":"<p>The following segments will assist you regarding the configuration about Java, Solr and Quick Start Wizard</p> <p>nopAccelerate Plus Pro Installation</p> <p>JAVA Setup</p> <p>SOLR Setup</p> <p>-What is SOLR ?</p> <p>-How to Start/Stop/Restart SOLR ?</p> <p>-Creating a new core</p> <p>-How to Delete core</p> <p>-How to Reload core</p> <p>-How to Delete indexed data</p> <p>-Start SOLR on system startup</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/","title":"nopAccelerate Plus Pro Installation","text":"<p>Follow the steps below to install and configure nopAccelerate Plus Pro easily:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#1-install-the-plugin","title":"1. Install the Plugin","text":"<p>Once you have downloaded the plugin successfully, install the plugin on your nopCommerce store.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#2-navigate-to-configuration","title":"2. Navigate to Configuration","text":"<p>After successful installation, go to:</p> <p>Administration \u2192 nopAccelerate Plus \u2192 nopAccelerate+ Search \u2192 Configure</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#3-add-license-keys","title":"3. Add License Keys","text":"<p>Enter the license keys provided to you via email.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#_1","title":"nopAccelerate Plus Pro Installation","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#4-getting-started-page","title":"4. Getting Started Page","text":"<p>Once license keys are added successfully, you will be redirected to the Getting Started page of the plugin.</p> <p>Here you will find two options to set up nopAccelerate Plus Pro:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#option-1-quick-wizard-setup","title":"Option 1: Quick Wizard Setup","text":"<p>If you click \u201cYes\u201d, you will be redirected to the Quick Wizard Setup, which will guide you to set up Solr and Java on your machine.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#option-2-manual-setup","title":"Option 2: Manual Setup","text":"<p>If you click \u201cNo thanks, I will set up manually\u201d, you will be redirected to the nopAccelerate configuration page, where you must set up Solr and Java manually.</p> <p>You can get guidance at: Java Setup and Solr Setup</p> <p>in this document to configure it manually.</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/","title":"Overview","text":"<p>Bundled Discounts Plug-in for nopCommerce enables the store owner to boost sales by offering discounts when customers purchase additional products along with the one they originally intend to buy.</p> <p>The store owner can create bundle(s) on a base product and set a discount amount that applies when the bundle is purchased.</p> <p>They can add discounts for bundles and link additional products to the base product within each bundle. The customer will receive the configured discount when buying that bundle.</p> <p>Customers can view bundle offers on the product details page of the base product. They can directly add bundle products to the cart from this page. If any bundle product has attributes, the plug-in will display a pop-up window for attribute selection.</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/features/","title":"Features","text":"<p>Features Enable/Disable Plug-in functionality. Enable/Disable dropping bundle related tables when un-installing the plug-in. Multi-store supported. Multi-currency supported. Create and manage various bundles and set bundle title as well as bundle name. Enable/Disable bundle and apply discount on bundle. Add bundle products to cart from bundle. Easy navigation to additional products. Auto update/delete of bundle discount on updating/deleting bundled product from the cart. Discount amount can or cannot be in percentage of bundle subtotal amount. Position your bundles' list on the basis of selected widget zone. Supported nopCommerce versions 3.70, 3.80, 3.90 and 4.00.</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/getting-started/","title":"Licensing","text":"<p>Getting started This section will guide you to plug-in installation steps, configuration and how to use plug-in.</p> <p>Installation &amp; License</p> <p>Configuration</p> <p>Scenarios of use</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/version-history/","title":"Overview","text":"<p>Version history This page contains version history information about plug-in. You can directly go to a version history details by clicking on a version link from below versions.</p> <p>Version 1.0.0</p> <p>Version 1.0.1</p> <p>Version 1.1.0</p> <p>Version 1.2.0</p> <p>Version 1.1.3</p> <p>Version 1.2.1</p> <p>Version 1.2.2</p> <p>Version 1.3.0</p> <p>Version 1.3.1</p> <p>Version 1.3.2</p> <p>Version 1.3.3</p> <p>Version 1.4.0</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/Version%20history/1.0.0/","title":"1.0.0","text":""},{"location":"bundleDiscount/Version%20history/1.0.0/#100","title":"1.0.0","text":"<p>!!! info \"Version Details\"     | Release Date | January 24, 2017 |     |------------------|------------------|     | Plug-In Version | 1.0.0 |     | Supported nopCommerce Version | 3.80 |</p> <p>Features:</p> <ul> <li>Create bundles with discount on base product and add product(s) to them.  </li> <li>Display active bundles to customers on product details page.  </li> <li>Add bundle to cart more than once.  </li> <li>Configure attributes for products of the bundle before adding them to cart.  </li> <li>Multi-currency support.  </li> <li>Multi-store support.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"displayReward/","title":"Overview","text":"<p>The Display Reward Points Plugin provides functionality for displaying reward points on product detail page that the customer will gain on buying the product. You can change location of displaying reward points via changing CSS selector and you can also change content and design of displaying reward points from plug-in configure page. </p> <p>Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.0/","title":"Version 1.0.0","text":""},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.0/#100","title":"1.0.0","text":"Release Date March 19, 2017 Plug-In Version 1.0.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 3.80"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ol> <li>Display reward point on product detail page.  </li> <li>Customizable CSS selector for the display reward point.  </li> <li>Customizable content and design of display reward point.  </li> <li>Multi-store Supported.  </li> </ol> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.1/","title":"1.0.1","text":"Release Date March 19, 2017 Plug-In Version 1.0.1 Supported nopCommerce Version 3.80"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.1/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ol> <li>Update user manual.  </li> <li>Added help document link in plug-in configure page.</li> </ol> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.1.0/","title":"1.1.0","text":"Release Date March 28, 2017 Plug-In Version 1.1.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 3.90"},{"location":"displayReward/1.1.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Upgraded to nopCommerce 3.90</li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.2.0/","title":"1.2.0","text":"Release Date February 01, 2018 Plug-In Version 1.2.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.00"},{"location":"displayReward/1.2.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Upgraded to nopCommerce 4.00</li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.3.0/","title":"1.3.0","text":"Release Date September 05, 2018 Plug-In Version 1.3.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"displayReward/1.3.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Added support for nopCommerce 4.10  </li> <li>Added Multi-Language support in 4.10  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.3.0/#bug-fix","title":"Bug Fix","text":"<ul> <li>Reward points calculation fixed for grouped products in 4.10</li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/49.0.0/","title":"49.0.0","text":"Release Date October 28, 2025 Plug-In Version 49.0.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.90"},{"location":"displayReward/49.0.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Upgraded to nopCommerce 4.90 </li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Configuration/","title":"Configuration","text":""},{"location":"displayReward/Configuration/#general-tab-configuration","title":"General Tab Configuration","text":"<p>This plug-in displays reward points on the product detail page that a customer would earn based on the product amount and the configured reward point settings.</p> <p>\u26a0\ufe0f Note: The plug-in will not work if reward points settings are disabled in nopCommerce. To enable reward point settings, go to: Configuration \u2192 Settings \u2192 Reward Points and enable it along with other reward point configurations.</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Configuration/#display-configuration","title":"Display Configuration","text":"<ul> <li> <p>You can choose where to display reward points for the product amount using \"CSS selector for Reward points\".   Reward points will appear after the element defined by your selector.</p> </li> <li> <p>You can customize the HTML content with inline CSS styles in the \"Display content\" text box as per your preference.</p> </li> </ul> <p>\ud83d\udca1 Important: It is mandatory to include the keyword <code>RewardPoints</code> in your text where you want the calculated reward points to appear. Without <code>RewardPoints</code>, only static text will be displayed on the product details page (no reward points will be shown).</p> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Feature/","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Display reward points on product detail page</li> <li>Display reward points on Grouped product detail page</li> <li>Automatically calculates reward points for products as per configuration of reward point</li> <li>Customizable CSS selector for the display reward points</li> <li>Customizable content and design of display reward points</li> <li>Multi-store Supported, Multi-Language Supported(nopCommerce-4.10), Supported version(s) </li> </ul> <p>Supported Version(s): 3.80, 3.90, 4.00, 4.10, 4.20, 4.30, 4.40, 4.50, 4.60 , 4.70, 4.80 and 4.90</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Help/","title":"How to Get Help","text":"<p>If you face any issues, you can:</p> <ul> <li>Email us at support@nopaccelerate.com</li> <li>Or use the support form: http://www.nopaccelerate.com/wiki/support</li> </ul> <p>You can also send us the exact steps to reproduce the issue by recording it using the Problem Steps Recorder (psr.exe) on Windows:</p> <ol> <li>Open Run in Windows and type <code>psr.exe</code>, then press Enter.</li> <li>Click Start Record and perform the steps that produce the issue.</li> <li>When done, click Stop Record.</li> <li>You will be prompted to save a .zip file.</li> <li>Email the saved .zip file to us along with a short description of the issue.</li> </ol> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous </p>"},{"location":"displayReward/History/","title":"Version History","text":"<p>This page contains version history information about plug-in. You can directly go to a version history details by clicking on a version link from below versions.</p> <p>Version 49.0.0</p> <p>Version 1.0.0</p> <p>Version 1.0.1</p> <p>Version 1.1.0</p> <p>Version 1.2.0</p> <p>Version 1.3.0</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Licence/","title":"Installation &amp; Licensing","text":"<p>Download the plug-in object code and place it in your Plugins folder, then follow the standard nopCommerce plug-in installation procedure.</p> <p>The Display Reward Points plug-in appears under the Promotions group on the Local plugins page.</p> <p>Once installed:</p> <ol> <li>Go to your nopCommerce Admin Panel.</li> <li>Navigate to: Configuration \u2192 Plugins \u2192 Local plugins \u2192 Display Reward Points plugin</li> <li>The plug-in will prompt you to enter your license key (as shown in the figure below).</li> <li>Enter the license key you received via email after purchasing the plug-in from our website.</li> </ol> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/senerioOfUse/","title":"Scenerios of Use","text":"<p>This section provides common usage scenarios for the Display Reward Points plug-in.</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/senerioOfUse/#product-detail-page","title":"Product Detail Page","text":"<p>Reward points are displayed on the product detail page.</p> <p> </p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/sub-child1/","title":"Sub child1","text":"<p>This sub child</p>"}]}
