{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"]},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"Available Plugins","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Display Reward Point</p> </li> <li> <p>Bundle Discount </p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/","title":"nopAccelerate Plus Pro","text":"<p>nopAccelerate Plus Pro helps businesses across the nopCommerce ecosystem create highly relevant, scalable, and lightning-fast in-site search and product discovery experiences.</p> <p>It is one of the Best Rich Search Plugins for nopCommerce stores. It integrates Apache Solr with nopCommerce to deliver outstanding features that enhance in-site product search.</p> <p>nopAccelerate Plus Pro brings powerful search technology that strengthens your eCommerce store search, ultimately improving user experience and driving customer satisfaction.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#why-nopaccelerate-plus-pro","title":"Why nopAccelerate Plus Pro?","text":"<ul> <li>Better and faster search results directly and positively impact sales.  </li> <li>Better Search = More Revenue!</li> <li>nopAccelerate Plus Pro is completely different from the original nopAccelerate.   Since 2013\u201314, nopCommerce has evolved significantly, allowing us to design an advanced, modern, and standard integration plugin.</li> <li>The product is now more compatible with themes and plugins, easier to extend, and simpler to maintain.</li> <li>It includes Search &amp; Facets features, making it more powerful than nopAccelerate Plus Search.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#core-features","title":"Core Features","text":"<ol> <li>DIH (Data Import Handler) indexing process for faster indexing.</li> <li>Reload Solr core directly from the admin panel.</li> <li>Automatic core setup (managed schema, DIH request, update dbConfig, schema management).</li> <li>Clear core data from the nopAccelerate Plus Pro admin panel.</li> <li>Execute Solr queries from the admin panel.</li> <li>Automatic indexing on entity change via a simple toggle setting.</li> <li>Direct DB update support with automatic incremental table update.</li> <li>Basic configuration panel integrated into nopCommerce admin.</li> <li>Single core for multi-language &amp; multi-store.</li> <li>API integration support.</li> <li>Advanced wizard for Solr setup &amp; product integration.</li> <li>Easy-to-follow product basics and admin settings tour.</li> <li>Zero theme customization required.</li> <li>Supports 36 languages out of the box.</li> <li>Fully compatible with NopTemplates themes.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#search-features","title":"Search Features","text":"<ol> <li>Replaces default nopCommerce search.</li> <li>Extensive configuration options for search relevancy.</li> <li>Advanced language analysis during search.</li> <li>Search across Meta Title, Description &amp; Keywords.</li> <li>Auto spell suggestions.</li> <li>Sorting options in search results.</li> <li>Infinite scrolling and pagination options.</li> <li>Fine-tuning search using Minimum Should Match.</li> <li>Highly relevant and advanced search functionality.</li> <li>Advanced autocomplete search with greater relevancy.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#catalog-features","title":"Catalog Features","text":"<ol> <li>Product navigation from Apache Solr.</li> <li>Layered / Faceted navigation.</li> <li>Enhanced Category, Manufacturer &amp; Tag pages via Solr.</li> <li>Configurable catalog listing options.</li> <li>Stay online during first-time full indexing.</li> <li>Support for default filters.</li> <li>Category page filters.</li> <li>Manufacturer page filters.</li> <li>Product Tag page filters.</li> <li>jQuery slider-based price range filter.</li> <li>Multi-select faceting.</li> <li>Enhanced faceting UI.</li> <li>Instant AJAX faceting.</li> <li>AJAX response caching.</li> <li>Solr request caching.</li> <li>Stock availability filter.</li> <li>Rating-based sorting.</li> <li>Mobile-responsive filters.</li> <li>Infinite scrolling on all catalog pages.</li> <li>State-aware URLs using HTML5 History API.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/#facet-features","title":"Facet Features","text":"<ol> <li>Price Range and Price Slot facet filters.</li> <li>Category, Manufacturer, Vendor &amp; Product Tag facet filters.</li> <li>Product Attribute &amp; Specification Attribute facet filters.</li> <li>Stock Availability filter.</li> <li>Product Rating facet filter.</li> <li>Instant AJAX faceting.</li> <li>Search within facet results.</li> <li>View More / View Less functionality for long facet lists.</li> <li>Default expanded or collapsed facet settings on page load.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1056/","title":"0.3.0.1056","text":"Release Date 06 June 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.1056 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1056/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Image Indexing using DIH instead of Atomic Updates.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1056/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Faceting checkboxes were overlapping \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Code refactoring improvements.</li> <li>Solr Down message appeared even when Solr was connected \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Search textbox placeholder was not inserting correct category or manufacturer names \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Throbber screen did not hide when Core Setup failed \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Vendor-updated price not showing in product box even when \u201cGet price from Solr\u201d was disabled \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Adding a review showed two product boxes \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>View mode change did not support theme-based design \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Mobile collapse issue \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Duplicate copyField destination records after Atomic Update via API \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Infinite scroll not working in IE \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Faceting broke when specification contained &amp; \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Toggle Faceting did not work with Default Theme \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Solr Down displayed even when plugin wasn\u2019t enabled for catalog \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Infinite scrolling failed on screen height ~625px \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Facet collapse issues on mobile \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>UI improvements for Clear All &amp; Clear facet links.</li> <li>Faceting failed on <code>%</code> character \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Missing CSS when using custom or no-template themes \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Searching with <code>tshirt</code> vs <code>tShirt</code> returned different results \u2014 standardized.</li> <li>Default pagination applied incorrectly when <code>AllowCustomersToSelectPageSize</code> was disabled \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Solr query returned only required fields instead of all \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Pagination issues with native theme \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>JavaScript error: <code>viewmode_href is undefined</code> in Venture Theme \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>RTL theme selection now respects nopAccelerate Plus theme naming.</li> <li>Product Status page: MarkAllAsPending, ImageStatus selected/deleted actions not working \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Catalog/Search page: tooltip duplicated across all products in multi-language \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Facet search not working with color squares \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Facet search not working in IE \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Using Facet Search removed \u201cmore\u201d option from other facets \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Adding Language did not correctly generate Managed Schema \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Adding Language did not install nopAccelerate Search resource values \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Enable/Disable facet setting did not work for Vendor &amp; ProductTag pages \u2014 resolved.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1056/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1056/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1056/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 as the managed schema structure has changed.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1115/","title":"0.3.0.1115","text":"Release Date 17th June 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.1115 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10, 4.20"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1115/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Implemented caching for fetching Manufacturer &amp; Category.</li> <li>Default images now load when products do not have assigned images.</li> <li>Clicking on facet values containing % was not working \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Minimum and maximum values were not being set in the price range \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Search boost with Meta Description, Keywords, and Title was not working \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>\u201cEnable Infinite Scrolling\u201d is now allowed only when \u201cEnable Ajax request\u201d is enabled.</li> <li>Searching category names with special characters (e.g., <code>companion'^%@s'</code>) now works properly.</li> <li>Price was incorrect after clicking a suggested keyword when spellcheck was used \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Changing the language now updates the price range correctly.</li> <li>Searching using GTIN number was not working \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Searching within facet filters with special characters now works correctly.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1115/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1115/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-installing-the-plugin-again","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and installing the plugin again?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 due to Stored Procedure changes and managed schema structure modifications.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.1115/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 the managed schema structure has changed.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.666/","title":"0.3.0.666","text":"Release Date 15 February 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.666 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.666/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Configure Page UI Enhancements for better usability.</li> <li>SEO-friendly URL structure added.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.666/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Import/Export for Catalog Settings not working correctly \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Catalog-wise settings not working for:  </li> <li>Enable Infinite Scrolling  </li> <li>Show Number of Products  </li> <li>Enable Ajax Request   \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>License Key Page for Search &amp; Catalog Plugin sometimes threw thread exceptions \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>General Settings tab moved to second position after Configure.</li> <li>Corrected spelling of Relevancy in sorting options on Catalog &amp; Search pages.</li> <li>Updated \u201cSeo\u201d to SEO in General Settings tab.</li> <li>If \u201cEnable Search\u201d is disabled, Search Boost tab &amp; other search-related options will now hide correctly.</li> <li>Catalog Settings now only appear when Catalog (Plus) is enabled.</li> <li>Incorrect searching for ProductAttributeValue &amp; SpecificationAttributeValue \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Incorrect count for \u201cNumber of Products Found\u201d when featured products were associated with a category \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Shorter parameter names introduced for facet URLs.</li> <li>Removed <code>Schedule_ManageIncrementalSolrProduct</code> and related button from Configure page.</li> <li>When Facet is disabled, nopCommerce native facets now load correctly and show results properly.</li> <li>Unified attribute delimiter: now using single URL attribute delimiter instead of three separate ones.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.666/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.666/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 because Catalog Settings were reorganized and moved, requiring a clean installation.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.666/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 managed schema structure changed, so re-indexing is required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.696/","title":"0.3.0.696","text":"Release Date 22 February 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.696 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.696/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Wizard text now comes from Resource Strings.</li> <li>Updated design of Wizard Setup Page.</li> <li>Facet settings are now separated from Catalog Settings.</li> <li>Added Export/Import functionality for Catalog Facet Settings.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.696/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Checkbox UI not showing correctly in Wizard Setup steps \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>\u201cShow number of products found\u201d not showing on page load even when enabled \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>No PriceFilter request triggered when searching with wrong keyword first time \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Remote Solr hosting on Wizard Setup now works correctly.</li> <li>SolrCore validation messages were not displaying \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Updated SiteMenu Resource Strings for both plugins.</li> <li>Special characters in URL caused issues \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Show/Hide functionality in Facet filter not working \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Product Attributes &amp; Specification Attributes appeared in facet even when category was not applied and attribute fetching from Solr was enabled \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Removed unwanted default NopCommerce constants.</li> <li>Replaced SweetAlert from Admin with native nopCommerce alerts.</li> <li>\u201cmm should match\u201d validation not working as expected \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Improved License page design.</li> <li>Wizard Setup &amp; Getting Started opened even without Search plugin license \u2014 fixed.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.696/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.696/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 because Facet Catalog Setting was implemented and requires a clean installation.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.696/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 managed schema structure changed, so re-indexing is required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.727/","title":"0.3.0.727","text":"Release Date 01 March 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.727 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.727/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Added ability for users to navigate back to Getting Started and Wizard Setup even after skipping it earlier.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.727/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Moved AjaxRequest Facet setting from Facet Settings to Search Settings.</li> <li>Updated Resource Strings and SiteMenu Resource Strings.</li> <li>Corrected sample URL format displayed in SEO settings.</li> <li>Fixed licensing issue in Catalog plugin when license expired.</li> <li>In nopAccelerate Plus Catalog Settings \u2192 Category tab:  </li> <li>\u201cShow No Of Product Founds\u201d \u2014 changed No to Number.  </li> <li>\u201cInfinite Scrolling Till Page\u201d \u2014 corrected spelling of \u201cnumaric\u201d to numeric.</li> <li>Wizard Setup \u2192 Download link was not redirecting properly \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Catalog Facet Settings should not be visible when Catalog Settings license is not activated \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Updated Wizard Setup form design.</li> <li>\u201cDid you mean\u201d section not showing on misspellings \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Default nopCommerce attribute filters displayed even when Catalog Facet Filters were enabled \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Store-wise settings not applying on frontend \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Obfuscation issue resolved.</li> <li>DIH indexing failed for some products due to ProductAttributeList &amp; SpecificationAttributeList \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Creating Managed Schema failed for sk and tn languages \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Price Slot Facet selection name now matches the display name used in the facet filter.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.727/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.727/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 because Facet Catalog Settings were implemented and require a clean installation.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.727/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 managed schema structure changed, so re-indexing is required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.744/","title":"0.3.0.744","text":"Release Date 08 March 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.744 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.744/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Added RTL (Right-To-Left) support for the Default Theme.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.744/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Fixed issue where the Price Slot Search Box was not functioning correctly.</li> <li>\u201cLess/More\u201d option not showing correct results after searching in Facet textbox \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Page number issue when page size changed \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Currency displayed in the price range slider differed from product section \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Fixed facet query issues involving strings containing commas (,).</li> <li>Synonyms file was not being generated or pushed to Solr \u2014 now handled by the plugin.</li> <li>Fixed selected Min &amp; Max value formatting issue.</li> <li>Missing link during Wizard Setup (Solr-to-SQL test) in Solr configuration step \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Removed unnecessary recurring method calls during facet URL preparation.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.744/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.744/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>No</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.744/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>No</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.805/","title":"0.3.0.805","text":"Release Date 17 March 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.805 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.805/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Added support for ActionFilter on Catalog Controller.</li> <li>Implemented Tour for Search Configuration page.</li> <li>Published event for Prepare Model of Catalog.</li> <li>Searching now supports SKU &amp; GTIN defined under Attribute Combinations.</li> <li>Performance improvement: made single request for search + facet operations.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.805/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Attributes were fetched using <code>categoryName</code> instead of <code>CategoryId</code> \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Unpublished Category, Manufacturer, Vendor, ProductAttribute &amp; SpecificationAttribute appeared in Facet filter \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>\u201cStop Indexing\u201d did not work during stopping cycle \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Removed previous incorrect implementation of indexing on entity change.</li> <li>Long Solr Query executions failed when passing values \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Removed code that unnecessarily fetched <code>PictureIds</code> from database.</li> <li>ProductAttribute &amp; SpecificationAttribute facets did not show correct product results or counts \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Fixed message formatting issue when importing settings with mismatched nopCommerce/nopAccelerate versions.</li> <li>Solr Down Message on header while admin logged in was implemented incorrectly \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>\u201cLess/More\u201d UI not rendering color-square properly \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Improved all Setup Wizard log messages.</li> <li>Fixed indexing progress showing more than 100%.</li> <li>Fixed String or Binary Data Truncated issue when storing SystemNames for activated WidgetNames.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.805/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.805/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.805/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.850/","title":"0.3.0.850","text":"Release Date 1 April 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.850 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.850/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Performance improvement: Single combined request for search + facet, improving response time.</li> <li>Selector configuration made dynamic, eliminating theme view customization in most cases.</li> <li>Added a setting to log Solr queries in nopCommerce system logs for debugging.</li> <li>Updated price range slider design with clean tooltip for min/max values.</li> <li>Improved mobile filter UI: slide-out menu leaves overlay space that closes when tapped.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.850/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Tours were not designed for mobile \u2014 now disabled for mobile screens.</li> <li>Added message showing indexing is in progress when user clicks \"Start Indexing\" while it\u2019s already running.</li> <li>\u201cAdd to Compare\u201d was still visible even when disabled in Catalog Settings \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>After saving settings in Catalog Settings &amp; Catalog Facet Settings, the working tab did not reload \u2014 now fixed.</li> <li>Price range slider now respects custom price formatting.</li> <li>Updated \u201cpowered by\u201d image in nopAccelerate Catalog &amp; Search admin.</li> <li>Added logs for indexing start, stop, and failure events.</li> <li>Improved design of License Page.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.850/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.850/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>No</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.850/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>No \u2014 existing Solr Core can be used. No re-indexing required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.862/","title":"0.3.0.862","text":"Release Date 5 April 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.862 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.862/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Added resource strings for all active languages.</li> <li>Added setting for storing Solr queries in Solr logs.</li> <li>Enabled Indexing on entity change.</li> <li>Added Solr Down message logging in Solr log.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.862/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>AutoComplete was not showing product results \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Solr search boosting query had issues with different language cultures \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Solr debug query was not returning results when passing a long Solr query string \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Last Attribute value missing in facet results even when Specification &amp; Product Attribute facets were enabled \u2014 corrected.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.862/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.862/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>No</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.862/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>No \u2014 existing Solr Core can be used. No re-indexing required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.925/","title":"0.3.0.925","text":"Release Date 24 April 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0.925 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.925/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Added 5-Star Rating display when a product has an average rating of 5.</li> <li>Added Setup Wizard step for remotely hosted Solr instances.</li> <li>Implemented Index on Entity Change event.  </li> <li>Enables near real-time indexing without waiting for scheduled tasks.  </li> <li>Works only after a full indexing.  </li> <li>Will not run during scheduled indexing.</li> <li>Performance improvement: Added setting for ignoring Last Shopping Page.</li> <li>Added Scroll to Top button on Search &amp; Catalog pages.</li> <li>Implemented automatic scroll-to-top after selecting a facet.</li> <li>Implemented Solr Down notification (admin only).  </li> <li>If Solr is down, fallback uses nopCommerce default search/catalog so visitors never see errors.</li> <li>Added dynamic theme compatibility fields (<code>ThemeFileName</code> &amp; <code>RtlThemeFileName</code>) to support custom themes.</li> <li>Added Search within Catalog for Category, Manufacturer, Vendor &amp; ProductTag pages.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.925/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Product box not displaying Call for Price \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Plugin invoked methods even when not installed \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Solr ping monitoring caused performance issues \u2014 replaced with faster implementation.</li> <li>Language analysis applied incorrectly to <code>nGram</code> fields, causing bad relevance \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Spell Check with multi-term search suggested incorrect terms \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>Price range filter had fixed size \u2014 now adapts to layout.</li> <li>Tooltip on price slider not positioned correctly \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Mark as Pending not working in Product Status \u2014 fixed.</li> <li>Product search inside Product Status page not working correctly \u2014 resolved.</li> <li>Wrong WidgetZone activated (Catalog instead of Search plugin) \u2014 corrected.</li> <li>\u201cNo Products Found\u201d page should not show price slider \u2014 fixed.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.925/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.925/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0.925/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Not required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0/","title":"0.3.0","text":"Release Date 08 February 2019 Plug-In Version 0.3.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Configuration Page UI Enhancements for cleaner and easier navigation.</li> <li>SEO Enhancements including No-Index handling and Canonical URL management.</li> <li>License implementation added for Catalog Plugin.</li> <li>Catalog Settings and Search Settings are now separated into dedicated sections.</li> <li>Introduced General Settings as a separate section (instead of Performance Settings).</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Proper implementation of Price Slot &amp; Price Range in Catalog Settings.</li> <li>Correct plugin version and naming for Catalog Plugin.</li> <li>Export settings now correctly include Catalog Settings in the export file.</li> <li>PageSize Options now work properly with Ajax Filters.</li> <li>ViewMode options now function correctly with Ajax Filters.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 because Catalog Settings were reorganized and moved.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.3.0/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-performing-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or performing re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 re-indexing is required.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.4.0/","title":"0.4.0","text":"Release Date 30th July 2019 Plug-In Version 0.4.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.20"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.4.0/#feature-highlights","title":"Feature Highlights","text":"<ul> <li>Added an option that allows store owners to give in-stock products higher relevancy in search results.</li> <li>Solr Down notification now supports multiple email addresses (comma-separated).</li> <li>New licensing system with Product Limit and Expiration Date.</li> <li>Performance: Added a setting to ignore AvailableStartDateTimeUtc &amp; AvailableEndDateTimeUtc, improving raw Solr query speed.</li> <li>Performance: Using baseController instead of basePublicController for searching products.</li> <li>Performance: AutoComplete search now loads within 50 ms.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.4.0/#bug-fixes","title":"Bug Fixes","text":"<ul> <li>Fixed: Convert-to-Decimal issue on non-English cultures \u2014 now works for all cultures.</li> <li>Fixed: Solr down alert not showing on frontend when admin was logged in.</li> <li>Fixed: Solr debug query throwing object-reference error when Solr is down.</li> <li>Fixed: \"Enable Ajax request\" must be enabled for \"Enable Infinite Scrolling\" \u2014 now handled correctly.</li> <li>Fixed: Catalog images not showing for the second store when plugin was active.</li> <li>Fixed: Images not loading in Product Box on catalog pages when using SSL.</li> <li>Fixed: Removed extra horizontal space from selected facet section.</li> <li>Fixed: Reload Core &amp; Core Setup failure when hostname contains \u201csolr\u201d in Solr Core URL.</li> <li>Fixed: Removed unused entities from <code>db-config.xml</code> except Product entity.</li> <li>Fixed: Missing button spacing on configuration page.</li> <li>Fixed: Core Setup AJAX failure when app is hosted in a virtual directory (e.g., <code>localhost/nopcommerce</code>).</li> <li>Fixed: Tour tooltip now appears only once when configuration page is opened for the first time in a week.</li> <li>Fixed: Added validation for plugin settings.</li> <li>Fixed: Spellcheck issues with SKU &amp; GTIN.</li> <li>Fixed: Products not marked as Pending after changing Specification Attribute Values.</li> <li>Fixed: Page number now includes <code>href</code> attribute for SEO when infinite scrolling is disabled.</li> <li>Fixed: Infinite Scrolling &amp; \"Display No. of Products Found\" failing when Facets were disabled.</li> <li>Fixed: Facet Filter widget zone selection not working on Catalog Pages.</li> <li>Fixed: Searching incorrectly considered HTML tags/styles in Full Description \u2014 now cleaned.</li> <li>Fixed: Broken license section UI when license expired or validation failed.</li> <li>Fixed: Infinite scrolling failing when \u201cInfinite Scrolling till Page\u201d was set to 1.</li> <li>Fixed: Mega menu issues when category page loaded via nopAccelerate with JS minification enabled.</li> <li>Fixed: Advanced Search option showing when searching products from nopAccelerate Plus \u2014 now hidden.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.4.0/#faqs","title":"FAQs","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.4.0/#does-this-release-require-uninstalling-and-reinstalling-the-plugin","title":"Does this release require uninstalling and reinstalling the plugin?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 due to changes in Stored Procedures &amp; managed schema structure.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/0.4.0/#does-this-release-require-setting-up-a-new-core-or-re-indexing","title":"Does this release require setting up a new core or re-indexing?","text":"<p>Yes \u2014 because the managed schema structure has changed.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Category%26ManufacutreNavigation/","title":"Category and Manufacturer Navigation not working","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Category%26ManufacutreNavigation/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>Category and Manufacturer Navigation are not working on our store.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Category%26ManufacutreNavigation/#cause-of-the-problem","title":"Cause of the Problem","text":"<p>The <code>currentCategoryId</code> parameter used to invoke the CategoryNavigation ViewComponent is always <code>0</code> when using nopAccelerate Plus.</p> <p>This happens because the controller name is not <code>catalog</code> anymore \u2014 nopAccelerate Plus overrides the default Catalog controller.</p> <p>As a result, the navigation components do not receive the correct category context.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Category%26ManufacutreNavigation/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>You need to update the controller reference in your NopCommerce theme file.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Category%26ManufacutreNavigation/#steps","title":"Steps","text":"<ol> <li> <p>Open the file: _ColumnsTwo.cshtml</p> </li> <li> <p>Replace the controller name with NopAcceleratePlusWebCatalog This will correctly load CategoryNavigation and Manufacturer Navigation while using the nopAccelerate Catalog Plugin. </p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ConnectToSolr/","title":"How can I connect to Solr?","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ConnectToSolr/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>How can I connect to Solr? It shows a connection issue.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ConnectToSolr/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>First, verify that your Solr Core URL is correct.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ConnectToSolr/#example","title":"Example","text":"<p>If your Solr core name is Solr_sample, then your Solr Core URL should be: http://localhost:8983/solr/Solr_sample</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ConnectToSolr/#make-sure","title":"Make Sure:","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Your Solr Core URL does not end with a <code>/</code> Correct: <code>http://localhost:8983/solr/Solr_sample</code> Incorrect: <code>http://localhost:8983/solr/Solr_sample/</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Remove <code>#</code> from the Solr Core URL if it exists.</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/","title":"Error while performing indexing using DataImportHandler","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>You receive the following error when trying to index data using DataImportHandler:</p> <p>com.microsoft.sqlserver.jdbc.SQLServerException: The TCP/IP connection to the host localhost, port 1433 has failed. Error: \"Connection refused: connect. Verify the connection properties. Make sure that an instance of SQL Server is running on the host and accepting TCP/IP connections at the port. Make sure that TCP connections to the port are not blocked by a firewall.\"</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>Follow the steps below to resolve this issue:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#1-open-sql-server-configuration-manager","title":"1. Open SQL Server Configuration Manager","text":"<p>Press Windows Key + R to open the Run dialog.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#2-run-the-configuration-manager-for-your-sql-server-version","title":"2. Run the Configuration Manager for your SQL Server version","text":"<p>Use the appropriate command:</p> <ul> <li><code>SQLServerManager15.msc</code> \u2192 SQL Server 2018  </li> <li><code>SQLServerManager14.msc</code> \u2192 SQL Server 2017  </li> <li><code>SQLServerManager13.msc</code> \u2192 SQL Server 2016  </li> <li><code>SQLServerManager12.msc</code> \u2192 SQL Server 2014  </li> <li><code>SQLServerManager11.msc</code> \u2192 SQL Server 2012  </li> <li><code>SQLServerManager10.msc</code> \u2192 SQL Server 2008  </li> </ul> <p></p> <p>Note: If SQL Configuration Manager is not found, verify your SQL Server installation.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#3-expand-sql-server-network-configuration","title":"3. Expand: SQL Server Network Configuration","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#4-enable-tcpip","title":"4. Enable TCP/IP","text":"<p>Right-click TCP/IP \u2192 select Enable.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ErrorWhileIndexing/#5-restart-sql-server-services","title":"5. Restart SQL Server Services","text":"<p>Restart the SQL service so changes take effect.</p> <p></p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/FacetFilterWith%25/","title":"Facet Filter with % does not work","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/FacetFilterWith%25/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>When I apply a facet that contains the % character, the facet results are not displayed correctly.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/FacetFilterWith%25/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>Solr does not support using <code>%</code> inside facet values`. If your facet value contains a %, Solr may fail to process it, causing the facet filter to behave incorrectly.</p> <p>To fix this:</p> <ul> <li>Avoid using <code>%</code> in facet values.</li> <li>Rename or clean the facet data to remove the <code>%</code> symbol.</li> </ul> <p>Once the <code>%</code> character is removed, faceting will work properly again.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/FontError/","title":"Font Error in Google Chrome: Refused to load the font","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/FontError/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>Google Chrome shows font-loading errors such as:</p> <p>Refused to load the font <code>&lt;URL&gt;</code> because it violates the following Content Security Policy directive: \"font-src *\"`.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/FontError/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>To fix this issue, disable Google Chrome Grammar. For more details, refer to the article below:</p> <p>https://stackoverflow.com/questions/45366744/refused-to-load-the-font-datafont-woff-it-violates-the-following-content</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Help/","title":"How to Get Help","text":"<p>Please drop us an email at support@nopaccelerate.com with the issues you're facing.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Help/#information-to-include-in-your-email","title":"Information to Include in Your Email","text":"<p>When you contact us, please include the following details:</p> <ol> <li>Your Order Number:</li> <li>Store's nopCommerce version:</li> <li>nopAccelerate Plus Plugin version:</li> <li>Store Admin credentials (if possible):</li> <li>Steps to reproduce the issue:</li> </ol> <p>It is helpful if you attach images or a screen-cast, so we can reproduce the issue at our end more easily.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Help/#sending-steps-to-reproduce-using-psr-problem-steps-recorder","title":"Sending Steps to Reproduce Using PSR (Problem Steps Recorder)","text":"<p>You can also send us detailed steps to reproduce the issue by using the built-in Windows tool.</p> <p>Follow these steps:</p> <ol> <li>Open <code>psr.exe</code> from Run in your Windows operating system.</li> <li>Click on the \u201cStart Record\u201d button and perform the steps to reproduce your issue.</li> <li>Click \u201cStop Record\u201d once you finish. It will ask you to save a .zip file.</li> <li>Send us the saved .zip file via email.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/","title":"JAVA Setup","text":"<p>To set up SOLR and nopAccelerate Plus on your machine, the first step is to install and configure Java. Follow the steps below:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#1-download-and-install-java","title":"1. Download and Install Java","text":"<p>Download JAVA Latest Version from here.</p> <p>Install the latest Java version. You may choose the version as per your system requirements, but we recommend using the Windows Offline (64-bit) installer.</p> <p>After successful installation, you can check the Java installation path:</p> <ul> <li> <p>For Windows 32-bit: <code>C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Java</code></p> </li> <li> <p>For Windows 64-bit: <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java</code></p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_1","title":"JAVA Setup","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#2-define-the-java_home-environment-variable","title":"2. Define the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> Environment Variable","text":"<p>Defining the <code>JAVA_HOME</code> variable helps SOLR locate the Java installation on your machine.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#a-open-environment-variable-settings","title":"a) Open Environment Variable Settings","text":"<p>Do one of the following:</p> <ul> <li> <p>Windows 7:   Right-click My Computer \u2192 Properties \u2192 Advanced System Settings</p> </li> <li> <p>Windows 8:   Control Panel \u2192 System \u2192 Advanced System Settings</p> </li> <li> <p>Windows 10 / 11:   Search for Environment Variables \u2192 Select Edit the system environment variables</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#b-click-the-environment-variables-button","title":"b) Click the Environment Variables button.","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_2","title":"JAVA Setup","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#c-under-system-variables-click-new","title":"c) Under System Variables, click New.","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_3","title":"JAVA Setup","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#d-add-the-java_home-variable","title":"d) Add the JAVA_HOME Variable","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Variable Name: <code>JAVA_HOME</code></p> </li> <li> <p>Variable Value:   Add your Java installation path, for example: <code>C:\\Program Files\\Java\\jre1.8.0_201</code></p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/JAVASetup/#_4","title":"JAVA Setup","text":"<p>Click OK. You will now see the newly added <code>JAVA_HOME</code> variable in the environment variables list.</p> <p></p> <p>You have successfully configured the Java environment variable.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/","title":"Licensing Issues","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#question-1","title":"**Question 1 **","text":"<p>What will happen when the license expires?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#solution","title":"Solution","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#subscription-license","title":"Subscription License","text":"<p>If your subscription license expires, the nopAccelerate Plus plugin will stop working. When this happens:</p> <ul> <li>Search &amp; Catalog pages will automatically fall back to default nopCommerce methods </li> <li>You will lose advanced search and drill-down filtering features on:</li> <li>Search Results</li> <li>Category Pages</li> <li>Manufacturer Pages</li> <li>Vendor Pages</li> <li>Product Tag Pages</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#download-license-perpetual-license","title":"Download License (Perpetual License)","text":"<p>If you are using a Download license:</p> <ul> <li>The nopAccelerate Plus plugin continues to work </li> <li>However, support &amp; updates stop after the license expiry</li> <li>You won\u2019t receive:</li> <li>Bug fixes  </li> <li>Improvements  </li> <li>New features  </li> </ul> <p>Recommended: Renew your download license annually to receive ongoing updates and support.</p> <p>You will also receive automatic email reminders before and after license expiration.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#question-2","title":"Question 2","text":"<p>What will happen if the license suddenly fails? Will it impact my website visitors?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#solution_1","title":"Solution","text":"<p>If a license failure occurs (e.g., validation issues, expired license, wrong domain):</p> <ul> <li>Your website visitors are NOT affected </li> <li>Your live store continues to run using default nopCommerce methods</li> <li>The plugin features stop only on:</li> <li>Search pages</li> <li>Catalog pages   \u2026 if the license is invalid or unauthorized</li> </ul> <p>Only the administration area will show license warnings.</p> <p>If your key was valid once and approved, temporary failures will not affect your visitors.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#question-3","title":"**Question 3 **","text":"<p>How will I get notified about license issues?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/LicensingIssues/#solution_2","title":"Solution","text":"<p>You will see a Warning Notification on top of:</p> <ul> <li>nopAccelerate Plus configuration pages  </li> <li>nopAccelerate settings pages  </li> </ul> <p>These warnings explain the exact license issue so you can take action.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/","title":"Responsive Filter Not Working with nopTemplate Theme","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>Responsive filters of nopAccelerate Plus are not working with nopTemplate themes?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>If the responsive filter isn't working with a nopTemplate theme, apply the CSS updates below.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#css-changes-themes","title":"CSS Changes \u2192 Themes","text":"<p>If you're using any of these nopTemplate themes, follow Section 1:</p> <ul> <li>Lighthouse  </li> <li>Alfresco  </li> <li>Jewelry  </li> <li>NeoFashion  </li> <li>Beauty  </li> <li>Fashion  </li> <li>Electronics  </li> <li>Shop All  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#ui-changes-themes-section-1","title":"UI Changes \u2192 Themes \u2192 Section 1","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#file-nopaccelerate-stylemincss","title":"File: <code>nopaccelerate-style.min.css</code>","text":"<ul> <li>Replace <code>max-width:1000px</code> with <code>max-width:767px</code></li> <li>Replace <code>min-width:1001px</code> with <code>min-width:768px</code></li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#file-nopaccelerate-stylertlmincss","title":"File: <code>nopaccelerate-style.rtl.min.css</code>","text":"<ul> <li>Replace <code>max-width:1000px</code> with <code>max-width:767px</code></li> <li>Replace <code>min-width:1001px</code> with <code>min-width:768px</code></li> </ul> <p>If you're not using any of the themes listed above, apply Section 2.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#ui-changes-themes-section-2","title":"UI Changes \u2192 Themes \u2192 Section 2","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#file-nopaccelerate-stylemincss_1","title":"File: <code>nopaccelerate-style.min.css</code>","text":"<ul> <li>Replace <code>max-width:1000px</code> with <code>max-width:1024px</code></li> <li>Replace <code>min-width:1001px</code> with <code>min-width:1025px</code></li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/ResponsiveFilter/#file-nopaccelerate-stylertlmincss_1","title":"File: <code>nopaccelerate-style.rtl.min.css</code>","text":"<ul> <li>Replace <code>max-width:1000px</code> with <code>max-width:1024px</code></li> <li>Replace <code>min-width:1001px</code> with <code>min-width:1025px</code></li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/","title":"SOLR Setup","text":"<p>To set up SOLR on your machine, follow the steps below:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#1-download-solr","title":"1. Download Solr","text":"<p>Go to this link and download Solr 8.11.0 or above:</p> <p>\ud83d\udc49 Download Solr</p> <p>Select the preferred file. We recommend downloading Solr 8.11.0 version.</p> <p>We are assuming you are installing this on Windows.</p> <p>Note: The <code>solr-version.zip</code> or <code>solr-version.tgz</code> files (where version is the version number, e.g., <code>7.5.0</code>) contain: - Apache Solr - HTML documentation - Solr tutorial  </p> <p></p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#_1","title":"Solr Setup Steps","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#2-copy-downloaded-solr-version","title":"2. Copy Downloaded Solr Version","text":"<p>Extract the downloaded file to a preferred location.</p> <p>We assume you extracted it to the C:\\ drive and named the folder Solr. So your Solr path becomes:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SOLRSetup/#_2","title":"Solr Setup Steps","text":"<p>Hence, Solr is downloaded and Java is set up. Now let's start Solr.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SearchWithSynonyms/","title":"How can I search with synonyms?","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SearchWithSynonyms/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>I have products with the name \"Laptop\", and the user types \"NoteBook\" in the search box. I want the search results to show Laptop products when someone searches for \"NoteBook\". How can I configure this in Solr, and which file should I modify?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SearchWithSynonyms/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>You need to add synonym mapping inside the synonyms.txt file.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SearchWithSynonyms/#1-locate-the-synonyms-file","title":"1. Locate the synonyms file","text":"<p>You can find it here:</p> <p>C:\\solr-6.4.2\\server\\solr\\conf\\synonyms.txt"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SearchWithSynonyms/#2-add-your-synonym-rule","title":"2. Add your synonym rule","text":"<p>Append the following line at the end of the file:</p> <p>This tells Solr that searching for NoteBook should return results for Laptop.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SearchWithSynonyms/#3-reload-your-solr-core","title":"3. Reload your Solr Core","text":"<p>Important: After modifying the synonyms file, you must reload the core for the changes to take effect.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/","title":"Setup core if your Solr is hosted on a shared server","text":"<p>If you are using a Shared Server for Solr, you need to perform additional setup steps for the Solr Core.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#steps","title":"Steps","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#1-configure-solr-core-url","title":"1. Configure Solr Core URL","text":"<ul> <li>Enter the remote Solr server URL in the Solr Core URL field.</li> <li>Save the configuration page.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#2-run-core-setup","title":"2. Run Core Setup","text":"<ul> <li>Click Core Setup.</li> <li>It may take some time.</li> <li>After completion:</li> <li>\u2714 Managed Schema  </li> <li>\u2714 Core Stream Body  </li> <li>\u2714 Pattern Handler  </li> <li>\u274c DB Config File  </li> <li>\u274c Request Handler  </li> <li>The red cross icons indicate some manual setup is required.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#manual-setup-steps-for-remote-solr-hosting","title":"Manual Setup Steps for Remote Solr Hosting","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#1-download-required-setup-files","title":"1. Download required setup files","text":"<ul> <li>Go to: nopAccelerate Plus \u2192 nopAccelerate+ Search \u2192 Configure</li> <li>Find Setup files download</li> <li>Click the download button to get a ZIP containing required files.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#2-copy-configuration-files","title":"2. Copy configuration files","text":"<p>Unzip the file \u2014 you will find 3 files:</p> <ul> <li><code>db-data-config.xml</code></li> <li><code>solrconfig.xml</code></li> <li><code>synonyms.txt</code></li> </ul> <p>Copy these files into the conf folder of your Solr data directory.</p> <p>After copying, Reload the Core from Solr Admin.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#3-install-microsoft-jdbc-driver","title":"3. Install Microsoft JDBC Driver","text":"<p>Solr needs the MS SQL JDBC driver to connect to SQL Server.</p> <ul> <li>Copy the file: <code>sqljdbc42.jar</code></li> <li>Paste it into Solr\u2019s dataimporthandler/lib folder.</li> </ul> <p>Example (Windows): C:\\solr-7.5.0\\contrib\\dataimporthandler\\lib</p> <p>Create the folder if it does not exist.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#4-reload-core-from-nopaccelerate","title":"4. Reload Core from nopAccelerate","text":"<ul> <li>Go back to the plugin Configure page.</li> <li>Click Reload to apply all manual changes.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SetupCoreOnSharedServer/#5-verify-core-setup","title":"5. Verify Core Setup","text":"<p>Return to Core Setup: - This time the Request Handler should show \u2714 correctly done. - Manually update <code>DbConfigFileStatus</code> to true. - Perform Indexing.</p> <p>If indexing works successfully, your remote Solr core setup is complete.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SolrService/","title":"Using Solr as a service in Windows Server","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SolrService/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>How can I run Solr as a Windows service on a Windows Server?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SolrService/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>To run Solr as a Windows service, follow the official guidelines provided here:</p> <p>(Insert your Solr service setup link here)</p> <p>This guide explains how to install, configure, and manage Solr so it runs as a background service.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SolrService/#things-to-take-care-of","title":"Things to Take Care Of","text":"<ul> <li> <p>Solr should not stop when you log off from the system.   Running it as a service ensures it stays active even after user logout.</p> </li> <li> <p>Solr must start automatically after system restart.   Make sure the service startup type is set to Automatic, and it restarts on the same port you configured.</p> </li> </ul>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/SupportDocOverview/","title":"Support Document","text":"<p>The following segments will assist you regarding the configuration about Java, Solr and Quick Start Wizard</p> <p>nopAccelerate Plus Pro Installation</p> <p>JAVA Setup</p> <p>SOLR Setup \u2013 What is SOLR ? \u2013</p> <p>How to Start/Stop/Restart SOLR ? \u2013</p> <p>Creating a new core \u2013</p> <p>How to Delete core \u2013</p> <p>How to Reload core \u2013</p> <p>How to Delete indexed data \u2013</p> <p>Start SOLR on system startup</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/Technical%20FAQ%27s/","title":"Technical FAQ's","text":"<p>The following segments will assist and redirect you about the common technical FAQ's: </p> <p>Error while performing indexing using DataImportHandler</p> <p>Setup core if your Solr is hosted on shared server</p> <p>How can I connect to Solr ?</p> <p>TimeOut Expiration Error on Plugin installation</p> <p>Category and Manufacturer Navigation not working</p> <p>How can I search with synonyms ?</p> <p>Facet Filter with % does not work</p> <p>Licensing Issues</p> <p>Responsive filter not working with noptemplate theme</p> <p>Font error in Google Chrome 'Refused to load the font <code>&lt;URL&gt;</code>'</p> <p>Implement WebRequest for StartIndexing method</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/TimeOutExpiration/","title":"TimeOut Expiration Error on Plugin installation","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/TimeOutExpiration/#question","title":"Question","text":"<p>I am getting the following error while installing the plugin:</p> <p>Timeout expired. The timeout period elapsed prior to completion of the operation or the server is not responding</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/TimeOutExpiration/#cause-of-the-problem","title":"Cause of the Problem","text":"<p>This issue occurs when there is a large amount of data, and during plugin installation the system attempts to create the Incremental_Table.</p> <p>While doing so, the stored procedure:</p> <p>NopAcc_Plus_ManageIncrementalSolrProductTable</p> <p>takes too long to execute and results in a timeout.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/TimeOutExpiration/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p>Follow the steps below:</p> <ol> <li> <p>Open the file: Plugin &gt; NopAcceleratePlus.Search &gt; SqlScript &gt; Sp_SolrInstall.sql</p> </li> <li> <p>Remove the following line from the script:</p> </li> </ol> <p>EXEC NopAcc_Plus_ManageIncrementalSolrProductTable</p> <ol> <li> <p>Manually execute the stored procedure directly in SQL Server:</p> </li> <li> <p>After the stored procedure completes successfully, install the plugin again.</p> </li> </ol>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/WebRequest/","title":"Implement WebRequest for <code>StartIndexing</code> Method","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/WebRequest/#questions","title":"Questions","text":"<p>How do you implement a WebRequest for the StartIndexing method?</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/WebRequest/#solution","title":"Solution","text":"<p><code>StartIndexing</code> is an async method, so when you trigger it, indexing runs in the background and does not affect your website traffic.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/WebRequest/#implementing-startindexing-get-method-in-a-third-party-tool","title":"Implementing <code>StartIndexing</code> (GET method) in a third-party tool","text":"<p>Implementing StartIndexing GET method in a third-party tool:</p> <p>```csharp string webAddr = \"/Admin/NopAcceleratePlusSearch/StartIndexing\"; <p>var httpWebRequest = (HttpWebRequest)WebRequest.Create(webAddr); httpWebRequest.ContentType = \"application/json\"; httpWebRequest.Method = \"GET\";</p> <p>HttpWebResponse httpResponse = (HttpWebResponse)httpWebRequest.GetResponse();</p> <p>if (httpResponse.StatusCode == HttpStatusCode.OK) {     using (var streamReader = new StreamReader(httpResponse.GetResponseStream()))     {         var responseText = streamReader.ReadToEnd();     } }</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/WebRequest/#notes","title":"Notes","text":"<p>Call this method after your updates are completed using any third-party tool, external script, or integration so your catalog achieves 100% indexing.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/","title":"nopAccelerate Plus Pro Installation","text":"<p>Follow the steps below to install and configure nopAccelerate Plus Pro easily:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#1-install-the-plugin","title":"1. Install the Plugin","text":"<p>Once you have downloaded the plugin successfully, install the plugin on your nopCommerce store.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#2-navigate-to-configuration","title":"2. Navigate to Configuration","text":"<p>After successful installation, go to:</p> <p>Administration \u2192 nopAccelerate Plus \u2192 nopAccelerate+ Search \u2192 Configure</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#3-add-license-keys","title":"3. Add License Keys","text":"<p>Enter the license keys provided to you via email.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#_1","title":"nopAccelerate Plus Pro Installation","text":""},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#4-getting-started-page","title":"4. Getting Started Page","text":"<p>Once license keys are added successfully, you will be redirected to the Getting Started page of the plugin.</p> <p>Here you will find two options to set up nopAccelerate Plus Pro:</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#option-1-quick-wizard-setup","title":"Option 1: Quick Wizard Setup","text":"<p>If you click \u201cYes\u201d, you will be redirected to the Quick Wizard Setup, which will guide you to set up Solr and Java on your machine.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/nopAcceleratePlusProInstallation/#option-2-manual-setup","title":"Option 2: Manual Setup","text":"<p>If you click \u201cNo thanks, I will set up manually\u201d, you will be redirected to the nopAccelerate configuration page, where you must set up Solr and Java manually.</p> <p>You can get guidance at: - Java Setup - Solr Setup</p> <p>in this document to configure it manually.</p>"},{"location":"NopAcceleratePlus/version-history/","title":"Version history","text":"<p>This page contains version history information about plug-in. You can directly go to a version history details by clicking on a version link from below:</p> <p>Version 0.4.0</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.1115</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.1056</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.925</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.862</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.850</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.805</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.744</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.727</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.696</p> <p>Version 0.3.0.666</p> <p>Version 0.3.0</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/","title":"Overview","text":"<p>Bundled Discounts Plug-in for nopCommerce enables the store owner to boost sales by offering discounts when customers purchase additional products along with the one they originally intend to buy.</p> <p>The store owner can create bundle(s) on a base product and set a discount amount that applies when the bundle is purchased.</p> <p>They can add discounts for bundles and link additional products to the base product within each bundle. The customer will receive the configured discount when buying that bundle.</p> <p>Customers can view bundle offers on the product details page of the base product. They can directly add bundle products to the cart from this page. If any bundle product has attributes, the plug-in will display a pop-up window for attribute selection.</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/features/","title":"Features","text":"<p>Features Enable/Disable Plug-in functionality. Enable/Disable dropping bundle related tables when un-installing the plug-in. Multi-store supported. Multi-currency supported. Create and manage various bundles and set bundle title as well as bundle name. Enable/Disable bundle and apply discount on bundle. Add bundle products to cart from bundle. Easy navigation to additional products. Auto update/delete of bundle discount on updating/deleting bundled product from the cart. Discount amount can or cannot be in percentage of bundle subtotal amount. Position your bundles' list on the basis of selected widget zone. Supported nopCommerce versions 3.70, 3.80, 3.90 and 4.00.</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/getting-started/","title":"Licensing","text":"<p>Getting started This section will guide you to plug-in installation steps, configuration and how to use plug-in.</p> <p>Installation &amp; License</p> <p>Configuration</p> <p>Scenarios of use</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/version-history/","title":"Overview","text":"<p>Version history This page contains version history information about plug-in. You can directly go to a version history details by clicking on a version link from below versions.</p> <p>Version 1.0.0</p> <p>Version 1.0.1</p> <p>Version 1.1.0</p> <p>Version 1.2.0</p> <p>Version 1.1.3</p> <p>Version 1.2.1</p> <p>Version 1.2.2</p> <p>Version 1.3.0</p> <p>Version 1.3.1</p> <p>Version 1.3.2</p> <p>Version 1.3.3</p> <p>Version 1.4.0</p>"},{"location":"bundleDiscount/Version%20history/1.0.0/","title":"1.0.0","text":""},{"location":"bundleDiscount/Version%20history/1.0.0/#100","title":"1.0.0","text":"<p>!!! info \"Version Details\"     | Release Date | January 24, 2017 |     |------------------|------------------|     | Plug-In Version | 1.0.0 |     | Supported nopCommerce Version | 3.80 |</p> <p>Features:</p> <ul> <li>Create bundles with discount on base product and add product(s) to them.  </li> <li>Display active bundles to customers on product details page.  </li> <li>Add bundle to cart more than once.  </li> <li>Configure attributes for products of the bundle before adding them to cart.  </li> <li>Multi-currency support.  </li> <li>Multi-store support.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"displayReward/","title":"Overview","text":"<p>The Display Reward Points Plugin provides functionality for displaying reward points on product detail page that the customer will gain on buying the product. You can change location of displaying reward points via changing CSS selector and you can also change content and design of displaying reward points from plug-in configure page. </p> <p>Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.0/","title":"Version 1.0.0","text":""},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.0/#100","title":"1.0.0","text":"Release Date March 19, 2017 Plug-In Version 1.0.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 3.80"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ol> <li>Display reward point on product detail page.  </li> <li>Customizable CSS selector for the display reward point.  </li> <li>Customizable content and design of display reward point.  </li> <li>Multi-store Supported.  </li> </ol> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.1/","title":"1.0.1","text":"Release Date March 19, 2017 Plug-In Version 1.0.1 Supported nopCommerce Version 3.80"},{"location":"displayReward/1.0.1/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ol> <li>Update user manual.  </li> <li>Added help document link in plug-in configure page.</li> </ol> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.1.0/","title":"1.1.0","text":"Release Date March 28, 2017 Plug-In Version 1.1.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 3.90"},{"location":"displayReward/1.1.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Upgraded to nopCommerce 3.90</li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.2.0/","title":"1.2.0","text":"Release Date February 01, 2018 Plug-In Version 1.2.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.00"},{"location":"displayReward/1.2.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Upgraded to nopCommerce 4.00</li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.3.0/","title":"1.3.0","text":"Release Date September 05, 2018 Plug-In Version 1.3.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.10"},{"location":"displayReward/1.3.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Added support for nopCommerce 4.10  </li> <li>Added Multi-Language support in 4.10  </li> </ul>"},{"location":"displayReward/1.3.0/#bug-fix","title":"Bug Fix","text":"<ul> <li>Reward points calculation fixed for grouped products in 4.10</li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/49.0.0/","title":"49.0.0","text":"Release Date October 28, 2025 Plug-In Version 49.0.0 Supported nopCommerce Version 4.90"},{"location":"displayReward/49.0.0/#features","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Upgraded to nopCommerce 4.90 </li> </ul> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Configuration/","title":"Configuration","text":""},{"location":"displayReward/Configuration/#general-tab-configuration","title":"General Tab Configuration","text":"<p>This plug-in displays reward points on the product detail page that a customer would earn based on the product amount and the configured reward point settings.</p> <p>\u26a0\ufe0f Note: The plug-in will not work if reward points settings are disabled in nopCommerce. To enable reward point settings, go to: Configuration \u2192 Settings \u2192 Reward Points and enable it along with other reward point configurations.</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Configuration/#display-configuration","title":"Display Configuration","text":"<ul> <li> <p>You can choose where to display reward points for the product amount using \"CSS selector for Reward points\".   Reward points will appear after the element defined by your selector.</p> </li> <li> <p>You can customize the HTML content with inline CSS styles in the \"Display content\" text box as per your preference.</p> </li> </ul> <p>\ud83d\udca1 Important: It is mandatory to include the keyword <code>RewardPoints</code> in your text where you want the calculated reward points to appear. Without <code>RewardPoints</code>, only static text will be displayed on the product details page (no reward points will be shown).</p> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Feature/","title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>Display reward points on product detail page</li> <li>Display reward points on Grouped product detail page</li> <li>Automatically calculates reward points for products as per configuration of reward point</li> <li>Customizable CSS selector for the display reward points</li> <li>Customizable content and design of display reward points</li> <li>Multi-store Supported, Multi-Language Supported(nopCommerce-4.10), Supported version(s) </li> </ul> <p>Supported Version(s): 3.80, 3.90, 4.00, 4.10, 4.20, 4.30, 4.40, 4.50, 4.60 , 4.70, 4.80 and 4.90</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Help/","title":"How to Get Help","text":"<p>If you face any issues, you can:</p> <ul> <li>Email us at support@nopaccelerate.com</li> <li>Or use the support form: http://www.nopaccelerate.com/wiki/support</li> </ul> <p>You can also send us the exact steps to reproduce the issue by recording it using the Problem Steps Recorder (psr.exe) on Windows:</p> <ol> <li>Open Run in Windows and type <code>psr.exe</code>, then press Enter.</li> <li>Click Start Record and perform the steps that produce the issue.</li> <li>When done, click Stop Record.</li> <li>You will be prompted to save a .zip file.</li> <li>Email the saved .zip file to us along with a short description of the issue.</li> </ol> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous </p>"},{"location":"displayReward/History/","title":"Version History","text":"<p>This page contains version history information about plug-in. You can directly go to a version history details by clicking on a version link from below versions.</p> <p>Version 49.0.0</p> <p>Version 1.3.0</p> <p>Version 1.2.0</p> <p>Version 1.1.0</p> <p>Version 1.0.1</p> <p>Version 1.0.0</p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/Licence/","title":"Installation &amp; Licensing","text":"<p>Download the plug-in object code and place it in your Plugins folder, then follow the standard nopCommerce plug-in installation procedure.</p> <p>The Display Reward Points plug-in appears under the Promotions group on the Local plugins page.</p> <p>Once installed:</p> <ol> <li>Go to your nopCommerce Admin Panel.</li> <li>Navigate to: Configuration \u2192 Plugins \u2192 Local plugins \u2192 Display Reward Points plugin</li> <li>The plug-in will prompt you to enter your license key (as shown in the figure below).</li> <li>Enter the license key you received via email after purchasing the plug-in from our website.</li> </ol> <p></p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/senerioOfUse/","title":"Scenerios of Use","text":"<p>This section provides common usage scenarios for the Display Reward Points plug-in.</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/senerioOfUse/#product-detail-page","title":"Product Detail Page","text":"<p>Reward points are displayed on the product detail page.</p> <p> </p> <p>\u2190 Previous | Next \u2192</p>"},{"location":"displayReward/sub-child1/","title":"Sub child1","text":"<p>This sub child</p>"}]}
